"title": "8616: prayerlessness",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8616",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Without prayer any relationship with God is impoverished because vital communication is lost.</p>\n<h2>Reasons for prayerlessness</h2>\n<h3>Unbelief</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps14:1-Ps14:4\">PSA 14:1–14:4</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps53:1-Ps53:4\">PSA 53:1–53:4</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job21:15\">JOB 21:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:11\">ROM 3:11</a></p>\n<h3>Self-reliance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:5\">JER 17:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph3:2\">ZEP 3:2</a></p>\n<h3>Worship of other gods</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:17-Deut32:18\">DEU 32:17–32:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:5-Jer2:6\">JER 2:5–2:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:8\">JER 2:8</a></p>\n<h3>Guilt as a result of disobedience</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:9-Gen3:12\">GEN 3:9–3:12</a> <em>Adam and Eve did not respond to their sin by praying. On the contrary they sought to hide from God</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah1:1-Jonah1:6\">JON 1:1–1:6</a> <em>Jonah tried to run away from God.</em></p>\n<h3>Tiredness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:45\">LUK 22:45</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:40\">MAT 26:40</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:37\">MRK 14:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:43-Matt26:45\">MAT 26:43–26:45</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:40-Mark14:41\">MRK 14:40–14:41</a></p>\n<h3>Discord in relationship</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:7\">1PE 3:7</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of prayerlessness</h2>\n<h3>Joshua, after a great victory</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:2-Josh7:5\">JOS 7:2–7:5</a> <em>Joshua devised his own plan in attacking Ai and did not seek the LORD until after he suffered a disastrous defeat.</em></p>\n<h3>King Ahaziah, turning to idols</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs1:16\">2KI 1:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs1:1-2Kgs1:6\">2KI 1:1–1:6</a></p>\n<h3>The nominal religion of Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:22\">ISA 43:22</a></strong> <em>This verse implies that prayer involves effort--the people only paid lip service to God.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:14\">ISA 1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa64:7\">ISA 64:7</a></p>\n<h3>Israel trusts in other people rather than God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:1-Isa30:2\">ISA 30:1–30:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa31:1\">ISA 31:1</a></p>\n<h3>Israel's failure to repent of their sins</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:13\">DAN 9:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:13\">ISA 9:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer5:3\">JER 5:3</a></p>\n<h3>The lack of an intercessor among God's people</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek22:30\">EZK 22:30</a></p>\n<h2>Consequences of prayerlessness</h2>\n<h3>Alienation from God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:6\">JHN 15:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps73:27\">PSA 73:27</a></p>\n<h3>God's judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph1:4-Zeph1:6\">ZEP 1:4–1:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer10:21\">JER 10:21</a></p>\n<h3>Disloyalty to Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:74\">MAT 26:74</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:71\">MRK 14:71</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:60\">LUK 22:60</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:27\">JHN 18:27</a> <em>Peter had previously failed to pray in Gethsemane.</em></p>\n<h3>Spiritual poverty</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:2\">JAS 4:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:15\">2KI 17:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:5\">JER 2:5</a></p>\n<h3>Ineffective ministry</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:12\">1SA 2:12</a> <em>This literally means they had no fellowship with the LORD</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam12:23\">1SA 12:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:4-John15:5\">JHN 15:4–15:5</a></p>\n<h3>Conflicts with others because of unfulfilled desires</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:1-Jas4:4\">JAS 4:1–4:4</a></p>",
